version: 1
display_name: VCFC-9X-000001 - The VMware Cloud Foundation SDDC Manager PostgreSQL service must limit the number of concurrent sessions.
global_description: |-
  Database management includes the ability to control the number of users and user sessions utilizing a database management system (DBMS). Unlimited concurrent connections to the DBMS could allow a successful denial-of-service (DoS) attack by exhausting connection resources, and a system can also fail or be degraded by an overload of legitimate users. Limiting the number of concurrent sessions per user is helpful in reducing these risks.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - VCFC-9X-000001
  srg:
    - SRG-APP-000001-DB-000031
  cci:
    - CCI-000054
  nist:
    - AC-10
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_sddc_manager_postgresql:
    type: custom
    desc: The VMware Cloud Foundation SDDC Manager PostgreSQL service must limit the number of concurrent sessions.
    control_id: VCFC-9X-000001
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      As a database administrator, perform the following at the command prompt:

      # /usr/pgsql/16/bin/psql -h localhost -U postgres -A -t -c "SHOW max_connections"

      Example result:

      100

      If "max_connections" is set to -1 or more connections are configured than documented, this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      Database management includes the ability to control the number of users and user sessions utilizing a database management system (DBMS). Unlimited concurrent connections to the DBMS could allow a successful denial-of-service (DoS) attack by exhausting connection resources, and a system can also fail or be degraded by an overload of legitimate users. Limiting the number of concurrent sessions per user is helpful in reducing these risks.
    remediation: |-
      As a database administrator, perform the following at the command prompt:

      # /usr/pgsql/16/bin/psql -h localhost -U postgres -c "ALTER SYSTEM SET max_connections = '100';"

      Restart the PostgreSQL service by running the following command:

      # systemctl restart postgres
